menu "breadboard: bb_tls_creds"

config BB_MQTT_TLS_ENABLE
    bool "Enable TLS for the MQTT sink"
    default n
    help
        Opt-in TLS for the MQTT sink (bb_mqtt_client).  Default OFF for the
        smallest firmware footprint; the OTA/update-check HTTPS path
        (esp_http_client crt-bundle) is independent of this gate.
        When OFF, a cfg.tls=true request degrades gracefully: the
        bb_tls_creds resolve and broker-verification blocks are skipped;
        the broker connection proceeds plaintext.

config BB_HTTP_TLS_ENABLE
    bool "Enable TLS for the HTTP sink"
    default n
    help
        Opt-in TLS for the HTTP telemetry sink (bb_sink_http).  Default
        OFF for the smallest firmware footprint; the OTA/update-check
        HTTPS path (esp_http_client crt-bundle) is independent of this
        gate.  When OFF, the bb_tls_creds resolve and ca/cert/key
        assignments are skipped; the HTTP session opens without TLS.

config BB_TLS_MUTUAL_ENABLE
    bool "Enable mutual TLS (client certificate + key)"
    default n
    depends on BB_MQTT_TLS_ENABLE || BB_HTTP_TLS_ENABLE
    help
        Opt-in mutual TLS: enables the client certificate and private key
        credential paths in both the MQTT and HTTP sinks.  Requires at
        least one of BB_MQTT_TLS_ENABLE or BB_HTTP_TLS_ENABLE.  When OFF
        bb_tls_creds skips cert/key resolve_one calls, saving RAM and NVS
        lookup work; only the CA is resolved.

config BB_TLS_CREDS_NVS_MAX_LEN
    int "Max bytes for a single TLS credential read from NVS"
    default 4096
    help
        Bounds the heap buffer used to read one PEM (ca/cert/key) from NVS.
        Larger client certificate chains may need more than 4096 bytes.
        Heap-tight boards without PSRAM can lower this value to reclaim RAM
        at the cost of rejecting oversized credentials.

endmenu
